T triplets. It triggers huge earthquakes by burrowing 60 miles underground."},{"version":"yellow","text":"A team of triplets that can burrow over 60 MPH. Due to this, some people think it's an earthquake."},{"version":"gold","text":"Its three heads bob separately up and down to loosen the soil nearby, making it easier for it to burrow."},{"version":"silver","text":"Extremely power\u00ad ful, they can DIG through even the hardest ground to a depth of over 60 miles."},{"version":"crystal","text":"These DIGLETT triplets dig over 60 miles below sea level. No one knows what it's like underground."},{"version":"ruby","text":"DUGTRIO are actually triplets that emerged from one body. As a result, each triplet thinks exactly like the other two triplets. They work cooperatively to burrow endlessly."},{"version":"sapphire","text":"DUGTRIO are actually triplets that emerged from one body. As a result, each triplet thinks exactly like the other two triplets. They work cooperatively to burrow endlessly."},{"version":"emerald","text":"Because the triplets originally split from one body, they think exactly alike. They work cooperatively to burrow endlessly through the ground."},{"version":"firered","text":"In battle, it digs through the ground and strikes the unsuspecting foe from an unexpected direction."},{"version":"leafgreen","text":"A team of DIGLETT triplets. It triggers huge earthquakes by burrowing 60 miles underground."},{"version":"diamond","text":"Its three heads move alternately, driving it through tough soil to depths of over 60 miles."},{"version":"pearl","text":"Its three heads move alternately, driving it through tough soil to depths of over 60 miles."},{"version":"platinum","text":"Its three heads move alternately, driving it through tough soil to depths of over 60 miles."},{"version":"heartgold","text":"Its three heads bob separately up and down to loosen the soil nearby, making it easier for it to burrow."},{"version":"soulsilver","text":"Extremely powerful, they